issues.body:
#68 changed the HPKE reference from RFC 9180 to draft-ietf-hpke-hpke.  This is inappropriate until the latter becomes an RFC, since the downward reference would prevent us from finishing.  We're also not using any functionality that is specific to draft-ietf-hpke-hpke.  Therefore, we need to change the reference back for now.

Also, #68 failed to include the history entry describing the change in draft -13.  When this fix is made, please also add the history entry.

@tireddy2, I'm assigning this to you since you created the PR that we need to revert part of.

