We still have some further alignment to cover, but it would be good to have no open PRs during the week of IETF.

And we can consider publishing a new version when the draft window opens up.

@ilaril I'm not hearing a concrete attack here.

If there were one, it would apply to the base HPKE spec, which says its ok to have both info and aad be empty.
If its ok in the base spec, its ok to use it to encrypt a cek.

```suggestion
